column5:
Fixed platform checks

Using `navigator.platform` instead of `navigator.appVersion`
Moved `is.thenable` from Array checks to Object checks
Ensure `is.odd` return true for negative odd. (#276)
Add null value tests for regexp check methods.
Standardize spacing, added .editorconfig and ESLint rule. (#265)
Check for undefined values on RegEx checks. (#263) (#264)

Adds is.not.opera() check in is.chrome() method (#254)

Fixes #253
Avoid false positive for iphone in Facebook in-app browser. [closes #247]
Allow ua related methods to work in Node. [closes #245]

bug fix for `is.infinite` (#243)

* bug fix for `is.infinite`

* added unit test for `is.infinite`

maintaining `half` an integer in `is.palindrome` (#240)

* maintaining `half` an integer in `is.palindrome`

* added test for `is.palindrome`

* using `Math.floor` instead of `<<`
Drop unsupported Node.js versions from travis.
Have travis cache the npm cache instead of node_modules.
Move methods to alphabetic order per category.
Update method param hints in readme.
`value:string` > `value:any` for ip, ipv4, ipv6 in README (#229)

preventing running off the array index in `is.sorted` (#216)

* preventing running off the array index in `is.sorted`

* added more tests for `is.sorted`
Only fallback to other checks if there is no compare helper.

adding support for `-` in `is.dateString` (#217)

* allowing dateString to be seperated with a `-`

* added tests for updated `is.dateString`

* updated README.md for `is.dateString`

* added more test for clarity

Readme sync (#215)

* updated README.md with `version` checks for `is.ie`, `is.chrome`, `is.firefox`, `is.edge`, `is.opera`, `is.safari`, `is.phantom`

* updated README.md for `is.socialSecurityNumber` (made dashes optional)

* updated README.md for `is.hexadecimal` (optional `0x` in starting)

* updated README.md for `is.palindrome` (detects palindromes with punctuation marks as well)

* updated README.md for browser checks: `string` > `number|string`

* updated README.md with `version` checks for `is.iphone`, `is.ipad`, `is.ipod`
Update build and test commands in readme.
Add support for detecting chrome/firefox on ios.
Cleanup param and var names to align closer to docs.
Add support for comparing version ranges to browser/device methods.
reducing undefined and null identity check with single equality check (#208)
Move NaN checks in `is.sameType` to the number branch of the method.

in is.under fix parameter name min -> max (#180)

The second parameter should be named max

remove 2nd parameter in capitolized and palindrome (#179)

the second parameters is not needed

Add ESLint and its infrastructure (#205)

- Add ESLint
- Add and setup pre-commit package to validate diffs before commit
- Add pragmas to code and fix issue with semilicon
Changed IP to use IPv4 and IPv6 internally (#206)
Ensure `is.palindrome` works with strings containing non-alphanumeric characters.
Ensure hex prefixed with `0x` is detected by `is.hexadecimal`.
Allow `is.js` to work in a webworker. [closes #189]
Avoid false positives for `is.safari` in chrome/firefox on ios. [closes #173]
Ensure `is.capitalized` works with strings containing consecutive spaces.
Added a new browser detection function for phantomjs (#181)
Make dashes optional for social security number. [closes #164]
Update contributing text for feature requests.
Modify wording to avoid highlighting error (#192)
Ensure is.js doesn't error in IE8.
Update Opera regexp to match lower case letters.
Remove `i` flags from regexes that are searching lowercased strings.
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/ironmaniiith/is.js into ironmaniiith-master
Fix odd check for non-integer values

Update version to 0.7.4

- This version fix dependency management issues
added is.edge() method for edge browser
Removed circular dependancy in UMD definition.
Merge branch 'urlRegexBugFix' of https://github.com/fslone/is.js into fslone-urlRegexBugFix

Merge pull request #123 from indus/patch-1

Update README.md

Update README.md

Would you mind to add this badge to your readme.  Its just a backlink and would help JS.ORG to get some attention.
Merge branch 'readme-improvements' of https://github.com/weblancaster/is.js into weblancaster-readme-improvements

Add a more verbose, easy to understand readme

added some improvements to make the contribution a bit easier and help decrease the time of looking around concentrating everything in the main place.

I would suggest to first merge PR #116
Adding stronger url regex validation to address the issues raised in bug #106

Build minified library 0.7.3

- Remove String.prototype.includes from is.includes (by codemonkey800)
- Support --use_strict in iojs runtime (by vdemedes)
- Add description, repository, bugs, and homepage to package.json (by jonhester)
- Replace vendor folder with npm modules for testing (by jonhester )
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/vdemedes/is.js into vdemedes-master
Merge branch 'vendor' of https://github.com/jonhester/is.js into jonhester-vendor
Merge branch 'package.json' of https://github.com/jonhester/is.js into jonhester-package.json
add repository, bugs, and homepage to package.json
replace vendor folder with npm modules for testing
update blackberry check to work for Blackberry 10 devices
make is.number return false for NaN

Typo ...

Typo on trailing dot after window
endWith should return false when  is not present in the original string
Added is.json() to check JSON type

is.touchDevice()

Browser/Vendor agnostic test if current device (in browser mode) is a
touch device (Phone, tablet, hybrid device in tablet mode, ...).
Useful to condition a Swipe instantiation, for exemple.

Fix Opera detection

This patch ensures Opera 12 and older versions are correctly detected.

Support Canadian postal code with spaces, like "L8V 3Y1"

Canada Post claims that:
"The Postal Code is a six-character uniformly structured, alphanumeric
code in the form “ANA NAN” where “A” represents an alphabetic character
and “N” represents a numeric character. "

http://www.canadapost.ca/tools/pg/manual/PGaddress-e.asp?ecid=murl10006450#1413985
IE 11 doesn't identifies itself with "msie" in the user-agent.
Add 'is.ip(), is.ipv4() and is.ipv6' methods in is.js & their tests in test/test.js

all, any, space

all and any - performance improvement
space - before the change, it would return true for all the strings that
start with a space. ' a' would pass the test.
